Name: Juho Kim
Comments: Since my paper's touching upon crowdsourcing, online video, and tutorials, there seem to be many papers that can potentially go together in a session. I'd personally like to see more video tagging related papers in my session.

I can understand how the papers that are offered are largely either dealing with photos or in a few cases long term deployments. 

However, this paper is mostly about the Slow Technology Design Research Program. It advances this research space by creating and deploying a prototype that involves photos, but the project is much more about broader design issues. It would be best suited to a 'critical perspectives on design' style session. Initially when at the PC meeting, in the program planning meeting specifically, I had grouped it into what was then called the 'Critical Design' session. I think the paper would be best suited for this session or one like it as the people attending the other papers in it would likely also find this one interesting and engaging. Thanks so much for attempting to group it together with these.
